This paper deals with stochastic shortest path MDPs, which are a widely studied problem class in AI and probabilistic planning. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes new MDP classes and algorithms for solving them, which involves optimization and search techniques, making cs.LG and cs.RO likely sub-categories as well. The paper also explores theoretical relationships between the proposed classes, which suggests that cs.SY could be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper conducts an empirical study, which involves implementation and experimentation, making cs.PL a possible sub-category.
